WEBVTT

00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:14.740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

00:00:18.940 --> 00:00:23.880
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

00:00:25.290 --> 00:00:29.260
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

00:00:31.920 --> 00:00:37.010
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

00:00:38.210 --> 00:00:43.120
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

00:00:44.650 --> 00:00:47.930
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

00:00:47.930 --> 00:00:51.000
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

00:00:51.710 --> 00:00:56.660
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

00:00:57.700 --> 00:01:00.880
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:04.160
♪The open sky rises high♪

00:01:04.700 --> 00:01:09.830
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

00:01:10.600 --> 00:01:13.860
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

00:01:13.860 --> 00:01:17.220
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

00:01:17.630 --> 00:01:23.300
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

00:01:23.710 --> 00:01:26.960
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

00:01:26.960 --> 00:01:30.290
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

00:01:30.690 --> 00:01:34.730
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

00:01:34.730 --> 00:01:35.980
=The Lead=

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:37.980
=Episode 2=

00:01:38.500 --> 00:01:40.900
That should set Huang Zhengjing straight.

00:01:41.940 --> 00:01:43.620
Let's see if he still spends all day

00:01:43.780 --> 00:01:45.300
having heart-to-hearts with women.

00:01:46.860 --> 00:01:48.100
What happened to your leg?

00:01:48.460 --> 00:01:49.580
I took a spill off my bike.

00:01:49.580 --> 00:01:51.580
I'm fine. Just a scrape,
no broken bones.

00:01:51.820 --> 00:01:53.740
You're always so reckless.

00:01:53.740 --> 00:01:55.380
You get hurt doing just about anything.

00:01:55.380 --> 00:01:56.820
Watch what you do. The kid's here.

00:02:02.700 --> 00:02:03.740
That's your sister's kid?

00:02:05.580 --> 00:02:07.620
Why is she dressed like a beggar?

00:02:09.060 --> 00:02:10.900
You didn't pick the kid up outside, did you?

00:02:12.900 --> 00:02:15.060
Raised herding sheep,
now she looks like one.

00:02:17.580 --> 00:02:18.820
Didn't you say

00:02:19.660 --> 00:02:20.980
she was pretty good-looking,

00:02:20.980 --> 00:02:23.540
and could sing and dance at school?

00:02:23.540 --> 00:02:25.420
That one didn't come. They sent another.

00:02:28.060 --> 00:02:28.980
This is Aunt Hua.

00:02:29.740 --> 00:02:31.700
Aunt Hua is the troupe's star performer.

00:02:32.140 --> 00:02:33.340
She'll be your teacher someday.

00:02:34.940 --> 00:02:35.780
This kid...

00:02:36.220 --> 00:02:37.300
I didn't agree to that.

00:02:38.340 --> 00:02:39.180
What's wrong with her?

00:02:40.300 --> 00:02:41.340
She's perfectly fine.

00:02:42.140 --> 00:02:43.500
Arms and legs all there.

00:02:44.620 --> 00:02:45.780
And she runs really fast.

00:02:45.780 --> 00:02:46.980
I can't even catch up to her.

00:02:47.220 --> 00:02:48.700
Then send her to sports school.

00:02:52.580 --> 00:02:53.580
How's her voice?

00:02:54.100 --> 00:02:55.300
Well, she's not mute.

00:02:57.980 --> 00:03:00.660
Huang Zhengjing held a meeting yesterday

00:03:01.020 --> 00:03:02.660
and said that this round of recruitment

00:03:03.420 --> 00:03:05.020
will treat internal
and external applicants equally,

00:03:05.580 --> 00:03:06.580
with no special favors for anyone.

00:03:07.900 --> 00:03:10.220
Sounds like that was aimed at you.

00:03:11.420 --> 00:03:13.140
You're always so full of yourself.

00:03:13.260 --> 00:03:15.620
Now they've got something on you, huh?

00:03:15.620 --> 00:03:16.460
When was I ever full of myself?

00:03:17.100 --> 00:03:18.420
You're quite arrogant.

00:03:18.420 --> 00:03:19.820
If he wants my respect,

00:03:19.820 --> 00:03:21.180
he should act like a real man first.

00:03:21.380 --> 00:03:23.020
When it's time to bow your head,

00:03:23.180 --> 00:03:24.500
don't be so stiff all the time,

00:03:24.500 --> 00:03:25.980
standing there all hard and rigid.

00:03:26.180 --> 00:03:27.980
I'll stay stiff. What's he gonna do?

00:03:28.460 --> 00:03:29.500
Nothing. He can't do a thing.

00:03:39.580 --> 00:03:40.620
Smells like goat droppings.

00:03:42.100 --> 00:03:43.660
Hasn't she bathed in a year?

00:03:46.100 --> 00:03:47.100
What's her name?

00:03:47.540 --> 00:03:48.380
Laidi.

00:03:48.980 --> 00:03:49.820
The full name?

00:03:50.180 --> 00:03:51.820
It's just Yi Laidi.

00:03:51.940 --> 00:03:52.940
That sounds so rustic.

00:03:54.620 --> 00:03:56.020
Let's give her a new name.

00:04:00.580 --> 00:04:01.820
Yi Qing'e.

00:04:05.020 --> 00:04:07.540
What does it mean?
Still thinking about her?

00:04:15.540 --> 00:04:17.380
All this old grime,

00:04:17.660 --> 00:04:19.260
we've got to scrub it all off.

00:04:28.380 --> 00:04:29.700
He's coming home next month.

00:04:32.060 --> 00:04:33.580
I'm going to ask him for a divorce.

00:04:41.460 --> 00:04:42.540
I'm talking to you.

00:04:44.340 --> 00:04:46.260
I need to clean up this wound.

00:04:54.420 --> 00:04:55.300
Hang in there.

00:04:55.420 --> 00:04:57.660
♪The red flag of great progress♪

00:05:02.620 --> 00:05:05.340
♪Waves in the wind♪

00:05:21.380 --> 00:05:35.620
♪Blue skies and water mirror the clouds♪

00:05:37.340 --> 00:05:38.180
Mi Lan.

00:05:38.540 --> 00:05:39.460
What are you doing?

00:05:39.700 --> 00:05:40.540
Sanyuan.

00:05:41.100 --> 00:05:43.300
Provincial leaders are coming tomorrow.

00:05:44.340 --> 00:05:45.660
Ms. Hua rehearses in the day,

00:05:46.300 --> 00:05:47.380
and I practice at night.

00:05:47.500 --> 00:05:49.860
You're singing
Xiang Yang Hong in the dark?

00:05:50.060 --> 00:05:50.940
Are you okay?

00:05:51.020 --> 00:05:51.900
Only with the lights off

00:05:52.260 --> 00:05:53.900
can I really feel it.

00:05:54.900 --> 00:05:55.740
Feel what?

00:05:57.100 --> 00:05:59.740
A whole crowd filling the seats below,

00:06:00.700 --> 00:06:02.020
listening as I perform opera.

00:06:05.980 --> 00:06:06.940
Stop talking about it.

00:06:07.140 --> 00:06:09.220
You're giving me chills.

00:06:09.540 --> 00:06:10.620
No wonder Gou said

00:06:10.620 --> 00:06:12.620
all kinds live in this courtyard.

00:06:13.780 --> 00:06:15.660
As long as I can be on stage,

00:06:16.140 --> 00:06:18.820
I'll sing for anyone, even spirits.

00:06:20.380 --> 00:06:21.700
I hurt my leg.

00:06:21.700 --> 00:06:23.060
I'll put on some gentian violet

00:06:23.060 --> 00:06:23.940
to avoid infection.

00:06:23.940 --> 00:06:25.060
You take your time singing.

00:06:25.420 --> 00:06:26.260
What happened to you?

00:06:28.940 --> 00:06:30.860
I fell and hurt my leg.

00:06:35.260 --> 00:06:36.540
That's pretty bad.

00:06:36.540 --> 00:06:37.780
Let me take you to the hospital.

00:06:37.900 --> 00:06:40.260
I'm tough. It's not that serious.

00:06:40.940 --> 00:06:42.620
Some medicine will do.

00:06:56.740 --> 00:06:58.620
Easy, easy. Be gentle, okay?

00:06:58.700 --> 00:06:59.620
So you do feel pain.

00:07:00.340 --> 00:07:01.580
You think I'm numb or what?

00:07:01.580 --> 00:07:03.900
Didn't you say you're tough?

00:07:04.460 --> 00:07:06.020
That should just feel numb, right?

00:07:06.740 --> 00:07:09.460
I go numb, but the flesh doesn't.

00:07:09.860 --> 00:07:11.780
- Hang in there.
- Easy, easy.

00:07:12.740 --> 00:07:13.580
Sanyuan,

00:07:13.740 --> 00:07:14.660
let me ask you something.

00:07:16.860 --> 00:07:18.780
How do you play that drum of yours?

00:07:18.940 --> 00:07:20.620
How does it hit someone's weak spot?

00:07:23.660 --> 00:07:25.220
Caixiang told me about it.

00:07:25.460 --> 00:07:28.660
She said your drum could hit her spot

00:07:28.660 --> 00:07:31.260
and make her want to sing out loud.

00:07:32.260 --> 00:07:33.620
What's that supposed to feel like?

00:07:36.060 --> 00:07:37.580
Don't listen to her nonsense.

00:07:38.260 --> 00:07:40.260
The way you put it gives me chills.

00:07:41.580 --> 00:07:43.820
A drumstick only hits the drumhead.

00:07:44.140 --> 00:07:45.380
How could it hit any weak spot?

00:07:52.260 --> 00:07:53.100
Just look at the wind.

00:07:59.060 --> 00:08:00.340
Easy, easy. Be gentle.

00:08:07.780 --> 00:08:08.980
Look at yourself now.

00:08:12.740 --> 00:08:14.180
You even cut her hair.

00:08:15.340 --> 00:08:17.420
See how nicely I fixed her up.

00:08:17.900 --> 00:08:20.300
She takes after her uncle.
Can't be too bad.

00:08:20.540 --> 00:08:21.900
She looks alright, I guess.

00:08:26.660 --> 00:08:27.660
Can you sing?

00:08:29.740 --> 00:08:30.740
Sing a song for me.

00:08:33.860 --> 00:08:35.380
Yeah, sing one for your aunt.

00:08:36.340 --> 00:08:37.940
Give Aunt Hua a little surprise.

00:08:37.940 --> 00:08:39.180
I Love Beijing Tian'anmen.

00:08:39.500 --> 00:08:40.340
Do you know that one?

00:08:43.380 --> 00:08:45.300
I Found a Penny by the Roadside.

00:08:50.340 --> 00:08:51.180
What a surprise.

00:08:51.540 --> 00:08:52.380
This kid's good.

00:08:52.660 --> 00:08:53.660
A blank sheet of paper.

00:08:53.660 --> 00:08:55.100
You can write or draw anything on it.

00:08:56.940 --> 00:08:58.700
Then why not turn in a blank test?

00:08:58.820 --> 00:09:00.140
That's not the same thing.

00:09:01.580 --> 00:09:03.020
This trainee recruitment round

00:09:03.620 --> 00:09:04.700
only comes once in ten years.

00:09:06.060 --> 00:09:08.340
I heard even people from the regions

00:09:08.340 --> 00:09:10.140
and the counties are all applying.

00:09:10.540 --> 00:09:11.940
There are only 30 spots.

00:09:11.940 --> 00:09:13.380
The competition is fierce.

00:09:13.900 --> 00:09:15.340
Keep that in mind.

00:09:16.660 --> 00:09:19.140
Even then, it needs a ruling.

00:09:20.140 --> 00:09:21.380
There are five chief examiners.

00:09:21.740 --> 00:09:23.700
One vote from you, one from me.

00:09:23.940 --> 00:09:25.100
One from Zhu Jiru.

00:09:25.220 --> 00:09:26.540
One from Director Glasses.

00:09:26.940 --> 00:09:28.340
Huang Zhengjing is just this.

00:09:28.460 --> 00:09:29.780
So his objection means nothing.

00:09:34.380 --> 00:09:35.220
What is it?

00:09:35.980 --> 00:09:37.820
Why does it still smell funky?

00:09:43.380 --> 00:09:44.220
There's nothing.

00:09:46.180 --> 00:09:47.220
Those clothes.

00:09:47.620 --> 00:09:48.460
Alright, alright.

00:09:48.580 --> 00:09:49.660
That pile of clothes there.

00:09:49.980 --> 00:09:50.820
Take those away, now.

00:09:54.340 --> 00:09:55.260
Go, go, go.

00:09:56.100 --> 00:09:57.020
Gotta toss them away.

00:09:59.860 --> 00:10:00.700
Where are you going?

00:10:10.860 --> 00:10:11.700
Master Song.

00:10:11.820 --> 00:10:12.980
Why are you sitting here?

00:10:15.460 --> 00:10:16.900
Why's the kid up the tree again?

00:10:17.380 --> 00:10:18.500
What a troublemaker.

00:10:18.820 --> 00:10:20.580
Go live in that tree if you can.

00:10:21.060 --> 00:10:21.940
What are you doing?

00:10:21.940 --> 00:10:23.340
Taking these old clothes

00:10:23.540 --> 00:10:25.020
and tossing them in the stove to burn.

00:10:25.100 --> 00:10:26.580
My niece is from the countryside.

00:10:26.740 --> 00:10:28.500
She can't bear to throw them out.

00:10:28.500 --> 00:10:29.380
I'll burn them.

00:10:29.380 --> 00:10:30.420
The stove's covered up.

00:10:30.420 --> 00:10:32.380
Just leave them there for now.

00:10:32.900 --> 00:10:34.020
Leave those clothes to me.

00:10:35.700 --> 00:10:37.300
What do you want with those rags?

00:10:37.300 --> 00:10:38.980
Shoes Bai can turn them into a costume.

00:10:41.980 --> 00:10:43.740
You're really hung up on those rags.

00:10:51.340 --> 00:10:52.180
Shoes Bai.

00:10:54.820 --> 00:10:55.660
Shoes Bai.

00:11:01.940 --> 00:11:02.900
What are you doing?

00:11:03.700 --> 00:11:05.100
Fixing the white-haired girl's wig.

00:11:05.300 --> 00:11:06.900
You look pretty scary.

00:11:07.220 --> 00:11:08.060
What is it?

00:11:08.620 --> 00:11:10.140
I'd like you to alter the kid's clothes.

00:11:10.740 --> 00:11:11.940
Hu Sanyuan's niece.

00:11:12.220 --> 00:11:13.180
She just got here today.

00:11:13.900 --> 00:11:15.940
These are her old clothes.
Use them to make a costume.

00:11:16.740 --> 00:11:17.940
Wash them first. They smell.

00:11:18.700 --> 00:11:19.540
Come on in.

00:11:25.060 --> 00:11:25.900
Come in.

00:11:29.060 --> 00:11:30.060
Take off your wig.

00:12:20.060 --> 00:12:24.500
(Xi)

00:12:33.700 --> 00:12:34.540
What are you doing?

00:12:38.780 --> 00:12:39.620
What is all this?

00:12:39.740 --> 00:12:40.900
You'll sleep against the wall.

00:12:41.420 --> 00:12:42.860
We have to get up early tomorrow.

00:12:42.860 --> 00:12:44.340
Aunt Hua will warm up your voice.

00:12:44.340 --> 00:12:45.700
Let the kid sleep with me.

00:12:45.980 --> 00:12:47.700
She's grown now.
She can't sleep with you.

00:12:48.060 --> 00:12:50.300
Those gossips will start talking again.

00:12:50.820 --> 00:12:52.140
Already covered in lice,

00:12:52.140 --> 00:12:53.540
and now you're afraid of getting bitten?

00:12:55.180 --> 00:12:56.020
Go.

00:13:09.580 --> 00:13:11.660
How did I end up with lice?

00:13:12.220 --> 00:13:15.700
♪Who helped us turn things around?♪

00:13:17.780 --> 00:13:21.140
♪Who helped set us free?♪

00:13:23.220 --> 00:13:25.860
♪Our dear PLA did♪

00:13:25.860 --> 00:13:28.420
♪And our savior, the CPC♪

00:13:34.140 --> 00:13:36.660
♪The soldiers and people are one family♪

00:13:36.660 --> 00:13:39.740
♪Let's help them wash their clothes♪

00:13:41.660 --> 00:13:42.580
Good.

00:13:42.580 --> 00:13:45.100
We give up, we give up, we give up!

00:13:46.980 --> 00:13:48.140
We're soaked.

00:13:48.380 --> 00:13:49.660
Think of it as a bath.

00:14:07.980 --> 00:14:09.180
Open the window.

00:14:09.260 --> 00:14:10.140
Open it.

00:14:16.100 --> 00:14:17.180
Where are you from?

00:14:17.380 --> 00:14:18.420
You're here for the troupe too?

00:14:21.100 --> 00:14:22.060
My name is Bayi.

00:14:22.500 --> 00:14:23.340
What's your name?

00:14:24.420 --> 00:14:25.540
How do they test you?

00:14:26.220 --> 00:14:27.140
I want to try out too.

00:14:28.020 --> 00:14:29.380
Why aren't you saying anything?

00:14:30.500 --> 00:14:31.620
Are you mute?

00:14:38.020 --> 00:14:38.860
Who's there?

00:14:41.140 --> 00:14:42.140
You scared me.

00:14:48.380 --> 00:14:49.260
What are you looking at?

00:14:49.660 --> 00:14:51.100
Keep staring, and I'll smash you.

00:14:55.140 --> 00:14:56.500
Since when did the yard

00:14:56.500 --> 00:14:58.100
get so many fools?

00:15:01.540 --> 00:15:05.660
♪In the dead of night♪

00:15:05.660 --> 00:15:10.620
♪We wait for dawn♪

00:15:10.620 --> 00:15:20.420
♪In winter, we wait for spring♪

00:15:20.940 --> 00:15:30.540
♪If we hope for the Red Army♪

00:15:30.980 --> 00:15:40.940
♪The hills bloom with Azalea♪

00:15:41.580 --> 00:15:51.580
♪If we hope for the Red Army♪

00:15:53.300 --> 00:15:54.140
What's with the smile?

00:15:54.900 --> 00:15:56.380
Don't listen, and don't learn it.

00:15:56.380 --> 00:15:57.980
That's a flirt's way of singing. Got it?

00:15:58.740 --> 00:15:59.620
Go to sleep.

00:15:59.620 --> 00:16:07.460
♪Azalea♪

00:17:12.660 --> 00:17:13.660
This is Mr. Qiu.

00:17:13.660 --> 00:17:15.460
Be sweeter when you see him.

00:17:15.740 --> 00:17:17.460
He handles meals. You'll eat well.

00:18:31.220 --> 00:18:32.700
Laidi, time to get up.

00:18:36.420 --> 00:18:37.260
Get up now.

00:18:47.020 --> 00:18:47.860
Up.

00:19:28.700 --> 00:19:30.740
From now on, warm up your voice

00:19:30.740 --> 00:19:31.580
every morning, got it?

00:19:32.380 --> 00:19:33.220
First thing,

00:19:33.220 --> 00:19:35.180
relax your facial muscles.

00:19:35.540 --> 00:19:36.940
Then we'll do a yawn.

00:19:37.220 --> 00:19:38.500
Come on, follow me.

00:19:41.340 --> 00:19:42.180
Open your mouth wide.

00:19:46.180 --> 00:19:47.660
Why do we yawn?

00:19:47.660 --> 00:19:48.980
You'll notice when you yawn,

00:19:48.980 --> 00:19:51.420
your soft palate,
that little dangly thing,

00:19:51.420 --> 00:19:52.260
does this.

00:19:52.460 --> 00:19:54.340
Then lower the back of your tongue.

00:19:54.340 --> 00:19:56.020
That way, the more you open up,

00:19:56.260 --> 00:19:57.380
the brighter your voice will be.

00:19:57.660 --> 00:19:58.500
Got it?

00:19:59.660 --> 00:20:01.780
She's talking to you. Stand up straight.

00:20:01.980 --> 00:20:03.060
Don't lean over there.

00:20:03.140 --> 00:20:04.660
Come on, yawn.

00:20:11.020 --> 00:20:12.580
This little rascal
climbed onto the roof.

00:20:13.220 --> 00:20:14.260
You'll fall and break your neck.

00:20:14.260 --> 00:20:15.100
Go on, move.

00:20:16.820 --> 00:20:17.660
Come on.

00:20:17.820 --> 00:20:18.660
Watch closely.

00:20:24.660 --> 00:20:25.820
Yawn. Open your mouth.

00:20:34.020 --> 00:20:35.540
This kid, make a sound.

00:20:36.300 --> 00:20:37.660
At home, you're always yelling.

00:20:38.220 --> 00:20:39.580
Make a sound. Open wider.

00:20:40.380 --> 00:20:41.740
Make a sound. Your aunt's teaching you.

00:20:42.140 --> 00:20:44.500
Did you bring me
a mute kid to teach opera?

00:20:44.660 --> 00:20:46.020
What nonsense. How is she mute?

00:20:46.700 --> 00:20:47.540
Make a sound.

00:20:50.940 --> 00:20:51.940
You two are really something.

00:20:51.940 --> 00:20:53.540
Having a mute kid perform opera?

00:20:53.540 --> 00:20:54.540
Get lost.

00:20:56.460 --> 00:20:57.460
Open your mouth wide.

00:20:57.540 --> 00:20:58.540
Open up. Open up.

00:20:59.980 --> 00:21:00.820
Call out.

00:21:00.820 --> 00:21:01.660
Hu Sanyuan.

00:21:02.940 --> 00:21:04.500
Section Chief Guo wants you
at the security office.

00:21:05.060 --> 00:21:06.260
Why all the fuss this early?

00:21:06.260 --> 00:21:07.100
It's a good thing.

00:21:12.820 --> 00:21:13.860
Learn properly from your aunt.

00:21:16.220 --> 00:21:17.380
Come on, yawn.

00:21:25.260 --> 00:21:26.860
Something big happened in the troupe

00:21:26.980 --> 00:21:27.820
yesterday, you know?

00:21:28.700 --> 00:21:29.540
Yeah, I know.

00:21:29.860 --> 00:21:32.060
I'm telling you, this is very serious.

00:21:33.580 --> 00:21:35.660
Framing and slandering
the Revolutionary Committee leaders

00:21:35.660 --> 00:21:37.420
constitutes a major
counter-revolutionary case.

00:21:37.580 --> 00:21:38.620
So what if it's serious?

00:21:38.620 --> 00:21:40.260
Why are you yelling at me?

00:21:40.500 --> 00:21:41.500
Director Huang said

00:21:41.860 --> 00:21:43.180
if the anonymous letter writer

00:21:43.380 --> 00:21:44.580
confesses voluntarily,

00:21:44.980 --> 00:21:46.660
it'll be dealt with
as an internal civil conflict.

00:21:46.660 --> 00:21:48.340
What if the writer doesn't confess?

00:21:48.620 --> 00:21:49.820
Then it's an enemy-people contradiction.

00:21:50.260 --> 00:21:51.380
Fine, I'll confess.

00:21:51.460 --> 00:21:52.460
I didn't write the letter.

00:21:52.460 --> 00:21:53.740
No idea who did.

00:21:53.740 --> 00:21:55.420
And if I did know, I wouldn't tell you.

00:21:55.820 --> 00:21:57.260
Come here and copy this letter for me.

00:21:57.260 --> 00:21:58.100
Why should I?

00:21:58.660 --> 00:22:00.660
I'm asking you
to assist the Security Section.

00:22:00.660 --> 00:22:01.780
And if I don't?

00:22:01.780 --> 00:22:03.900
Then go to the Public Security Bureau.

00:22:04.620 --> 00:22:06.100
Alright, alright, you win. You're tough.

00:22:27.340 --> 00:22:28.340
Just hear me out.

00:22:28.780 --> 00:22:29.620
What?

00:22:30.940 --> 00:22:32.260
You're not up to this.

00:22:32.260 --> 00:22:33.700
Hand it to the police.

00:22:36.900 --> 00:22:37.980
(East wind blows,
war drums roll)

00:22:37.980 --> 00:22:38.940
(Who in the world fears any soul?)

00:22:38.940 --> 00:22:40.180
East wind blows...

00:22:40.180 --> 00:22:41.300
You scoundrel!

00:22:42.260 --> 00:22:43.380
Needs a good talking-to.

00:22:44.220 --> 00:22:47.500
♪Socialism is good, so great♪

00:22:47.860 --> 00:22:51.500
♪Our people stand tall in this state♪

00:22:51.700 --> 00:22:53.740
♪Old hostile forces fell in defeat♪

00:22:53.740 --> 00:22:57.540
♪Foreign intruders fled in retreat♪

00:22:57.540 --> 00:23:00.380
♪All folk throughout the land unite♪

00:23:00.380 --> 00:23:04.980
♪Build socialism with all our might♪

00:23:05.540 --> 00:23:06.380
Here.

00:23:07.420 --> 00:23:08.260
Take a bite.

00:23:11.180 --> 00:23:12.020
Come on.

00:23:12.420 --> 00:23:13.340
Three steamed buns.

00:23:14.180 --> 00:23:15.020
Hu Sanyuan.

00:23:15.620 --> 00:23:17.900
How long's your niece staying?

00:23:17.900 --> 00:23:18.780
What's wrong?

00:23:18.780 --> 00:23:21.180
Meals at the canteen cost money.

00:23:21.180 --> 00:23:22.580
Put it on your tab.

00:23:22.580 --> 00:23:24.180
I'll settle it when I'm paid.

00:23:25.300 --> 00:23:27.180
She's counted at the adult rate.

00:23:27.420 --> 00:23:28.300
Why is that?

00:23:28.300 --> 00:23:29.660
She's still just a little kid.

00:23:30.140 --> 00:23:32.780
You're even scheming money off a kid.

00:23:33.380 --> 00:23:35.420
Other kids can, but not yours.

00:23:36.980 --> 00:23:37.820
What does it mean?

00:23:38.900 --> 00:23:39.980
What does that mean?

00:23:43.980 --> 00:23:45.220
Slow down, slow down.

00:23:47.020 --> 00:23:47.860
Here.

00:23:54.340 --> 00:23:55.620
What are you all looking at?

00:23:55.620 --> 00:23:56.500
Watching the kid eat.

00:23:57.300 --> 00:23:58.140
Let her eat.

00:23:59.420 --> 00:24:01.420
Why watch a kid eat steamed buns?

00:24:02.300 --> 00:24:03.140
Eat.

00:24:05.100 --> 00:24:05.980
Hurry up.

00:24:05.980 --> 00:24:06.820
Come on, hurry up.

00:24:06.820 --> 00:24:08.540
Okay, okay, here, take it.

00:24:08.540 --> 00:24:09.380
Hurry up.

00:24:09.900 --> 00:24:10.740
What are you doing?

00:24:10.740 --> 00:24:11.820
We're making a bet

00:24:11.820 --> 00:24:12.980
over a pack of cigarettes.

00:24:13.500 --> 00:24:14.380
Betting on what?

00:24:14.380 --> 00:24:15.620
How many steamed buns she can eat.

00:24:15.620 --> 00:24:17.020
How many steamed buns can she eat?

00:24:20.380 --> 00:24:21.220
How many has she had?

00:24:21.220 --> 00:24:22.060
Five.

00:24:22.500 --> 00:24:23.540
She's had five buns?

00:24:23.980 --> 00:24:25.300
Five of these big steamed buns?

00:24:25.500 --> 00:24:26.380
Don't eat any more.

00:24:35.260 --> 00:24:36.220
Director Zhu is here.

00:24:38.140 --> 00:24:39.300
Tang, well,

00:24:39.780 --> 00:24:40.780
could you step out for a moment?

00:24:40.900 --> 00:24:43.060
I need to discuss
something with Director.

00:24:43.060 --> 00:24:43.900
Come on, quick, quick.

00:24:43.900 --> 00:24:44.780
What's it?

00:24:44.780 --> 00:24:45.620
Something important.

00:24:45.620 --> 00:24:46.500
Right, right, right.

00:24:46.500 --> 00:24:47.340
Okay.

00:24:48.220 --> 00:24:49.060
Here.

00:24:53.780 --> 00:24:54.700
What's this?

00:24:57.140 --> 00:24:58.060
(Certificate: Yi Laidi
of Ningzhou County)

00:24:58.060 --> 00:24:59.460
(Needs to join the County
Opera Troupe tryout)

00:24:59.460 --> 00:25:00.700
(Jiuyangou People's Commune
Revolutionary Committee)

00:25:08.780 --> 00:25:10.460
She's your own niece?

00:25:10.580 --> 00:25:12.060
Family ties run deep.

00:25:12.060 --> 00:25:13.020
So of course she's close.

00:25:15.460 --> 00:25:16.700
As of now,

00:25:16.700 --> 00:25:18.740
our troupe has over 300 kids signed up.

00:25:19.500 --> 00:25:21.220
We're only taking 30.

00:25:21.220 --> 00:25:22.300
That's one in a hundred.

00:25:22.780 --> 00:25:24.260
There are people
from every side above us,

00:25:24.260 --> 00:25:26.220
making calls and sending notes.

00:25:26.220 --> 00:25:27.300
There aren't enough spots.

00:25:27.500 --> 00:25:29.620
Zhu, you can't do me this small favor?

00:25:30.820 --> 00:25:32.540
What's the kid's family background?

00:25:33.380 --> 00:25:34.340
She's from a poor

00:25:35.020 --> 00:25:36.180
and lower-middle peasant family.

00:25:36.460 --> 00:25:37.460
Can she sing?

00:25:37.460 --> 00:25:38.340
She can.

00:25:38.340 --> 00:25:39.300
She sings and dances at home.

00:25:39.300 --> 00:25:40.700
Why not let the kid answer for herself?

00:25:42.580 --> 00:25:43.420
Don't be scared.

00:25:44.260 --> 00:25:46.420
If you can sing, sing one for me.

00:25:46.620 --> 00:25:47.620
Even humming would do.

00:25:47.860 --> 00:25:48.700
She can't sing.

00:25:50.060 --> 00:25:52.420
She just got here yesterday.

00:25:52.420 --> 00:25:53.460
Got carsick on the way.

00:25:53.580 --> 00:25:55.060
It left her feeling run-down.

00:25:55.220 --> 00:25:56.740
Her throat hurts so much

00:25:56.740 --> 00:25:57.580
that she can barely speak.

00:25:57.900 --> 00:25:59.540
Don't worry, she's not mute.

00:26:00.020 --> 00:26:01.900
None of those 300-plus kids are mute.

00:26:02.540 --> 00:26:04.340
People live off what's around them.

00:26:04.620 --> 00:26:06.060
Those closest get the first chance.

00:26:06.660 --> 00:26:07.980
When any workplace is hiring,

00:26:08.340 --> 00:26:10.140
don't they favor their own kids first?

00:26:10.940 --> 00:26:11.940
Good that you're here.

00:26:12.740 --> 00:26:14.140
Director Huang asked me to tell you,

00:26:15.500 --> 00:26:16.940
you and Hua Caixiang won't join

00:26:17.140 --> 00:26:19.140
the trainee recruitment work.

00:26:19.740 --> 00:26:20.580
Why not?

00:26:20.740 --> 00:26:22.860
The anonymous letter caused trouble.

00:26:23.020 --> 00:26:24.660
Hua Caixiang isn't fit
to be an examiner.

00:26:26.020 --> 00:26:27.780
Hua Caixiang's innocent, right?

00:26:28.540 --> 00:26:29.460
You know very well

00:26:29.740 --> 00:26:31.020
what kind of person she is.

00:26:31.020 --> 00:26:32.740
So what if I do know?

00:26:34.340 --> 00:26:35.300
And why can't I join?

00:26:36.100 --> 00:26:37.940
They need politically
conscious examiners.

00:26:38.140 --> 00:26:39.100
I'm not that kind of examiner?

00:26:39.100 --> 00:26:40.540
You don't get to decide that.

00:26:40.540 --> 00:26:41.660
What I say doesn't count either.

00:26:41.860 --> 00:26:43.620
You're the kid's uncle.
Do you think it's proper

00:26:43.620 --> 00:26:44.740
for you to be the examiner?

00:26:44.740 --> 00:26:46.740
What's improper about that? I...

00:26:49.940 --> 00:26:50.780
Come on.

00:26:51.060 --> 00:26:52.540
Let's register her first.

00:26:59.660 --> 00:27:01.540
Don't worry. I'll make sure you pass.

00:27:03.860 --> 00:27:04.700
Hu Sanyuan.

00:27:09.540 --> 00:27:10.740
The kid's clothes are ready.

00:27:14.060 --> 00:27:14.940
What's this?

00:27:15.620 --> 00:27:16.460
It's for the kid.

00:27:17.340 --> 00:27:18.340
Go on, say thank-you.

00:27:18.780 --> 00:27:19.620
You're welcome.

00:27:19.700 --> 00:27:20.540
Thanks.

00:27:28.460 --> 00:27:29.740
Who'd they swap us out for?

00:27:31.940 --> 00:27:33.540
He Dachui and Mi Lan.

00:27:36.140 --> 00:27:36.980
Where are you going?

00:27:36.980 --> 00:27:38.060
I'm gonna find Huang Zhengjing.

00:27:38.780 --> 00:27:40.900
Why do you flare up so fast?

00:27:41.060 --> 00:27:42.140
What do you mean, flare up?

00:27:42.140 --> 00:27:43.180
He's clearly pushing us around.

00:27:43.180 --> 00:27:44.580
He really thinks I'm a pushover.

00:27:44.580 --> 00:27:45.420
Alright, alright.

00:27:46.380 --> 00:27:47.780
No one's treating you like a pushover.

00:27:48.860 --> 00:27:50.300
They see you as a tough woman,

00:27:50.460 --> 00:27:52.660
waiting for you to take him on.

00:27:52.780 --> 00:27:53.820
If I don't take him down, I...

00:27:53.820 --> 00:27:55.140
Alright, alright. Calm down.

00:27:55.140 --> 00:27:56.220
Calm down.

00:27:56.860 --> 00:27:57.700
Let it go.

00:27:58.220 --> 00:27:59.060
Fine, fine.

00:28:00.740 --> 00:28:02.860
Being an examiner means nothing to me.

00:28:03.380 --> 00:28:04.460
What did Sly Zhu say?

00:28:04.460 --> 00:28:05.300
What was his attitude?

00:28:05.460 --> 00:28:06.940
He didn't say a thing.

00:28:07.820 --> 00:28:09.060
If he said anything more,

00:28:09.260 --> 00:28:10.660
he wouldn't be Sly Zhu.

00:28:11.660 --> 00:28:12.700
He Dachui,

00:28:13.380 --> 00:28:14.860
Huang Zhengjing's favorite.

00:28:15.260 --> 00:28:17.460
Mi Lan's on Huang Zhengjing's side too.

00:28:17.580 --> 00:28:19.660
Zhu Jiru goes with the wind.

00:28:19.660 --> 00:28:22.580
Only Director Glasses has some loyalty.

00:28:22.580 --> 00:28:23.460
Just a little, though.

00:28:25.180 --> 00:28:26.060
What's the count now?

00:28:29.020 --> 00:28:30.300
It's still four to one.

00:28:30.700 --> 00:28:31.980
It's turned around now.

00:28:32.980 --> 00:28:34.020
Keep being arrogant then.

00:28:36.220 --> 00:28:38.580
Why won't you say anything?

00:28:39.220 --> 00:28:40.460
Is speaking up that hard?

00:28:40.460 --> 00:28:42.020
Why are you yelling at the kid?

00:28:42.620 --> 00:28:44.260
Can't you see we two

00:28:44.260 --> 00:28:46.060
are worried sick over your issue?

00:28:46.500 --> 00:28:48.220
If you won't speak,
the score means nothing.

00:28:48.300 --> 00:28:50.460
In this situation,
talking won't help either.

00:28:51.260 --> 00:28:52.580
Let's hurry and figure this out.

00:28:56.540 --> 00:28:57.980
The three of us split the work.

00:28:58.900 --> 00:29:01.220
You get to open up and sing.

00:29:01.700 --> 00:29:03.900
You teach her to sing properly.

00:29:04.100 --> 00:29:05.500
I'll handle the rest.

00:29:05.500 --> 00:29:07.100
I just can't believe it.

00:29:07.540 --> 00:29:10.860
♪In the dead of night♪

00:29:10.860 --> 00:29:11.700
Sing it louder.

00:29:11.700 --> 00:29:15.580
♪We wait for dawn♪

00:29:15.580 --> 00:29:19.300
♪In winter♪

00:29:19.580 --> 00:29:20.500
Sing it out.

00:29:20.500 --> 00:29:23.460
♪We wait for spring♪

00:29:23.740 --> 00:29:26.540
♪If we hope for♪

00:29:26.540 --> 00:29:27.380
Ms. Mi Lan.

00:29:29.780 --> 00:29:30.620
Caixiang.

00:29:31.820 --> 00:29:32.780
Congratulations.

00:29:33.020 --> 00:29:34.340
You're even an examiner now.

00:29:34.900 --> 00:29:36.580
Director Huang told me last minute.

00:29:36.580 --> 00:29:38.380
I wasn't mentally ready for this.

00:29:38.380 --> 00:29:39.380
So what's going on here?

00:29:40.140 --> 00:29:41.340
This is Hu Sanyuan's niece.

00:29:41.820 --> 00:29:43.100
She wants to try for the troupe.

00:29:43.100 --> 00:29:44.780
I brought her to test her vocal range.

00:29:47.700 --> 00:29:48.940
Whose child is she?

00:29:50.980 --> 00:29:51.820
Hello, Ms. Hua.

00:29:51.820 --> 00:29:53.900
I'm Chu Jiahe. I'm twelve this year.

00:29:54.100 --> 00:29:55.140
I've seen you perform opera.

00:29:55.140 --> 00:29:56.300
I really look up to you.

00:29:58.300 --> 00:30:00.700
The girl's quite bright-looking.

00:30:00.700 --> 00:30:02.620
And she's quick with words too.

00:30:02.860 --> 00:30:03.980
That's thanks to my teacher.

00:30:04.260 --> 00:30:05.700
It's more about your family guidance.

00:30:06.180 --> 00:30:08.220
Her dad is a county official.

00:30:08.300 --> 00:30:09.900
Her mom works at
the County Bureau of Culture.

00:30:09.980 --> 00:30:11.420
She wants to join the troupe too.

00:30:11.780 --> 00:30:13.700
Director Huang asked me

00:30:13.700 --> 00:30:15.180
to coach her properly.

00:30:15.180 --> 00:30:17.220
Nice. You're teaching students now.

00:30:17.580 --> 00:30:18.700
I'm just helping out.

00:30:19.060 --> 00:30:21.300
Main thing is, this kid's got talent.

00:30:21.300 --> 00:30:22.540
A real promising one.

00:30:24.900 --> 00:30:26.020
Then you two carry on.

00:30:26.100 --> 00:30:27.220
You teach first.

00:30:27.540 --> 00:30:28.540
Take a break

00:30:28.540 --> 00:30:29.700
and learn well, okay?

00:30:29.700 --> 00:30:30.540
Okay.

00:30:30.860 --> 00:30:33.100
(The city girl, as pretty as a flower)

00:30:33.180 --> 00:30:37.220
(and with a voice
straight out of the radio)

00:30:37.620 --> 00:30:39.540
(was like a mirror)

00:30:39.540 --> 00:30:42.020
(that stripped the shepherd girl)

00:30:42.020 --> 00:30:43.580
right back to her true self.)

00:30:47.380 --> 00:30:50.300
(In winter, we hope for the Red Army)

00:30:51.220 --> 00:30:52.060
Do you know it?

00:30:53.820 --> 00:30:54.660
Say something.

00:30:56.820 --> 00:30:57.860
You don't know this?

00:30:58.700 --> 00:31:00.100
Is she nervous?

00:31:00.860 --> 00:31:02.620
Chu Jiahe, give her a demo.

00:31:04.580 --> 00:31:12.420
Do re mi fa so la.

00:31:12.540 --> 00:31:15.260
This is one, two, three,
four, five, six, seven.

00:31:15.260 --> 00:31:16.100
Got it?

00:31:18.300 --> 00:31:21.060
Her voice is a little tight.

00:31:21.700 --> 00:31:23.220
And the range isn't that high either.

00:31:23.300 --> 00:31:25.300
A bit like yours, kind of a thin voice.

00:31:26.820 --> 00:31:27.900
Pretty annoying, right?

00:31:28.820 --> 00:31:30.220
Hey, you and me,

00:31:31.220 --> 00:31:32.220
let's go work on posture.

00:31:37.060 --> 00:31:38.020
Listen to me.

00:31:38.460 --> 00:31:40.540
Breath support is key to perform opera.

00:31:41.180 --> 00:31:43.780
Every time you sing, inhale first.

00:31:44.460 --> 00:31:46.180
Then sink the breath to dantian.

00:31:46.660 --> 00:31:50.140
Let it pass the abdomen, chest, throat,

00:31:50.140 --> 00:31:51.460
then throw it out.

00:31:52.060 --> 00:31:53.740
If you're singing high notes,

00:31:53.740 --> 00:31:57.620
it also goes through the nose, head,

00:31:57.780 --> 00:31:59.820
and out through here.

00:32:00.340 --> 00:32:01.780
Throw it as far as you can

00:32:01.780 --> 00:32:03.540
and as loud as you can.

00:32:03.540 --> 00:32:04.380
Watch me.

00:32:04.940 --> 00:32:05.820
Got it?

00:32:05.820 --> 00:32:06.780
Give it a try.

00:32:06.980 --> 00:32:07.820
Come on.

00:32:07.940 --> 00:32:09.020
Let's sing it together.

00:32:09.980 --> 00:32:11.100
Come on, take a breath.

00:32:11.780 --> 00:32:16.540
One, two, three.

00:32:16.540 --> 00:32:17.380
Sing.

00:32:22.340 --> 00:32:23.780
What's wrong? What's wrong?

00:32:23.780 --> 00:32:24.620
A snake.

00:32:26.380 --> 00:32:27.780
Nobody move. Stay still.

00:32:28.180 --> 00:32:29.020
Laidi!

00:32:29.500 --> 00:32:30.460
Laidi!

00:32:35.260 --> 00:32:36.100
You...

00:32:51.940 --> 00:32:54.700
♪Your kid is impressive♪

00:33:07.740 --> 00:33:08.740
It's not even dry yet.

00:33:10.860 --> 00:33:12.300
I heard you dare catch snakes.

00:33:13.500 --> 00:33:14.340
You can catch a snake,

00:33:14.340 --> 00:33:15.940
so why can't you speak up?

00:33:18.580 --> 00:33:20.060
You're not really mute, are you?

00:33:20.940 --> 00:33:23.140
It's okay. I have no friends here.

00:33:23.260 --> 00:33:24.140
You don't have one either, right?

00:33:25.140 --> 00:33:25.980
Let's be friends.

00:33:26.820 --> 00:33:27.780
My name is Bayi.

00:33:28.020 --> 00:33:29.940
Come on, follow me.

00:33:43.220 --> 00:33:44.460
Here, eat this.

00:33:44.660 --> 00:33:46.260
I've hidden lots of roasted potatoes.

00:33:46.540 --> 00:33:47.620
If you're hungry, dig here.

00:33:47.940 --> 00:33:49.100
I want to try for the troupe too.

00:33:49.540 --> 00:33:51.100
I can do martial arts. Look.

00:33:54.540 --> 00:33:55.620
Hey, what are you doing?

00:33:56.220 --> 00:33:57.100
A whole pot of steamed buns.

00:33:57.620 --> 00:33:59.620
You ruined a whole pot of steamed buns.

00:33:59.700 --> 00:34:00.660
You can't even tend the fire right.

00:34:00.660 --> 00:34:01.700
What can you do, then?

00:34:02.060 --> 00:34:04.140
I don't want to tend fires.
I wanna perform.

00:34:04.300 --> 00:34:06.020
You can't even roast a sweet potato.

00:34:06.020 --> 00:34:07.260
Dream on.

00:34:07.260 --> 00:34:08.260
Why does she get to?

00:34:08.460 --> 00:34:09.580
Her uncle is the drum accompanist.

00:34:10.140 --> 00:34:11.500
Your dad's just a cook.

00:34:11.940 --> 00:34:12.780
Tell me why.

00:34:12.940 --> 00:34:14.220
You can't sing, so I'll do it.

00:34:14.820 --> 00:34:17.220
♪Back when my old unit♪

00:34:17.220 --> 00:34:18.900
Shut it, you troublemaker.

00:34:18.900 --> 00:34:19.740
What are you doing?

00:34:19.740 --> 00:34:20.740
What?

00:34:20.820 --> 00:34:21.820
I'm just singing a little.

00:34:23.900 --> 00:34:25.020
I'm leaving.

00:34:25.820 --> 00:34:26.940
I'll deal with you, you punk.

00:34:28.380 --> 00:34:29.220
Kid.

00:34:29.780 --> 00:34:31.180
Go this way. It's shorter here.

00:34:32.700 --> 00:34:33.540
Tell your uncle

00:34:33.860 --> 00:34:34.860
we're having meat today.

00:34:35.060 --> 00:34:36.340
Tell him to come early.

00:34:40.260 --> 00:34:41.260
Did you hear me?

00:34:45.220 --> 00:34:46.660
Why's this kid mute?

00:34:50.500 --> 00:34:51.980
How can a mute kid try for the troupe?

00:34:54.020 --> 00:34:56.380
Master Song, the coal's burnt out.

00:34:56.380 --> 00:34:57.780
Why aren't you helping me?

00:34:57.780 --> 00:34:58.860
- I'm cutting meat. My hands are full.
- Hurry up.

00:34:58.860 --> 00:35:00.500
Come on, open this steamer for me.

00:35:00.500 --> 00:35:01.340
Come on, come on.

00:35:02.540 --> 00:35:03.380
Master Song.

00:35:03.660 --> 00:35:06.260
Li and Zhang are here to help.

00:35:06.540 --> 00:35:07.780
- You two made it.
- Welcome, welcome.

00:35:07.980 --> 00:35:09.740
Welcome, welcome.

00:35:09.740 --> 00:35:10.580
Here.

00:35:11.380 --> 00:35:12.220
Master Song.

00:35:12.380 --> 00:35:13.220
This meat looks good.

00:35:14.820 --> 00:35:15.660
What is it?

00:35:15.820 --> 00:35:18.140
Slice it a little thinner.

00:35:21.180 --> 00:35:22.060
This thin works?

00:35:22.060 --> 00:35:23.100
- Where is it?
- Right here.

00:35:23.100 --> 00:35:23.940
Where is it?

00:35:23.940 --> 00:35:24.780
There is no meat left.

00:35:24.780 --> 00:35:25.860
You sliced it all up.

00:35:26.820 --> 00:35:28.300
You sure do talk a lot of nonsense.

00:35:28.460 --> 00:35:30.500
Qiu, go peel some scallions, hurry.

00:35:30.580 --> 00:35:31.820
Potatoes. Okay, okay.

00:35:31.820 --> 00:35:33.020
You want it thinner?

00:35:33.020 --> 00:35:34.460
Once it's all stirred up, you miss it.

00:35:35.260 --> 00:35:36.260
Can't help it.

00:35:36.620 --> 00:35:38.100
There are too many people around.

00:35:38.740 --> 00:35:39.900
If they don't see meat in the bowl,

00:35:39.900 --> 00:35:41.380
they will start complaining.

00:35:41.900 --> 00:35:43.020
Neither plain food nor rich fare

00:35:43.020 --> 00:35:44.340
can ever please them.

00:35:45.900 --> 00:35:46.740
People

00:35:46.740 --> 00:35:48.620
never really feel satisfied inside.

00:35:48.860 --> 00:35:50.420
There's never enough people.

00:35:50.420 --> 00:35:52.220
They keep saying add more staff.

00:35:52.220 --> 00:35:53.700
You can't keep asking for help.

00:35:53.700 --> 00:35:54.620
They'll come when it's time.

00:35:54.700 --> 00:35:55.540
Don't worry.

00:35:57.380 --> 00:35:58.220
Master Song.

00:35:59.100 --> 00:35:59.940
Thinner.

00:36:01.660 --> 00:36:04.060
Tell me why you stay quiet.

00:36:06.100 --> 00:36:09.300
Do you know why I had you
learn to perform opera?

00:36:10.340 --> 00:36:13.100
Life in Jiuyangou was too hard for you.

00:36:15.100 --> 00:36:16.740
And your mom had
a little brother for you.

00:36:17.940 --> 00:36:19.620
It'd be even harder to feed you.

00:36:20.620 --> 00:36:22.900
Before, I helped your mom and dad.

00:36:23.900 --> 00:36:25.500
But I'm not that young anymore.

00:36:25.780 --> 00:36:27.300
One day, I'll have my own family too.

00:36:27.380 --> 00:36:28.500
I won't be able to help you then.

00:36:28.900 --> 00:36:29.740
What will you do then?

00:36:30.660 --> 00:36:31.700
If you get into the troupe,

00:36:31.700 --> 00:36:33.100
you've got to help your mom and dad.

00:36:33.100 --> 00:36:35.060
You'll need to support the whole family.

00:36:35.700 --> 00:36:37.260
That'd be helping me too, got it?

00:36:39.100 --> 00:36:40.380
Just say something.

00:36:41.100 --> 00:36:43.420
If you speak up and still aren't cut out

00:36:43.780 --> 00:36:45.460
for perform opera or this line of work,

00:36:45.660 --> 00:36:46.900
then I can let it go.

00:36:47.660 --> 00:36:49.860
Okay? Say something.

00:36:53.260 --> 00:36:54.660
You're driving me crazy.

00:36:58.900 --> 00:36:59.980
We're having meat today.

00:37:02.020 --> 00:37:03.420
They told you to go early.

00:37:07.100 --> 00:37:07.940
Who said that?

00:37:08.940 --> 00:37:12.300
Bayi's dad.

00:37:13.180 --> 00:37:14.020
See?

00:37:14.460 --> 00:37:15.940
You finally said something.

00:37:16.660 --> 00:37:18.020
Was talking really that hard?

00:37:19.340 --> 00:37:21.940
But I didn't mean talking about meat.

00:37:23.180 --> 00:37:24.580
If you get into the opera troupe,

00:37:24.580 --> 00:37:27.020
I'm telling you,
we'll have meat every week.

00:37:27.780 --> 00:37:29.780
One meat meal every week, got it?

00:37:30.100 --> 00:37:32.580
Did you get what I said?

00:37:34.740 --> 00:37:36.900
When you're out there, can you talk?

00:37:40.660 --> 00:37:42.220
Come on, move. We're having meat today.

00:37:42.220 --> 00:37:43.100
Coming, coming.

00:37:43.100 --> 00:37:44.540
(Who would've thought)

00:37:44.860 --> 00:37:46.580
(all that coaxing and scaring failed,)

00:37:46.580 --> 00:37:47.820
(Today's Menu)
(but a meat meal)

00:37:48.300 --> 00:37:51.620
(Pork Stew, Shredded Potatoes)
got Yi Qing'e to finally speak.

00:37:51.620 --> 00:37:52.980
Everyone's smelling the meat.

00:37:53.860 --> 00:37:55.220
What's going on? Why isn't it open yet?

00:37:55.540 --> 00:37:56.380
Hu Sanyuan!

00:37:56.380 --> 00:37:57.220
It's open.

00:37:57.420 --> 00:37:58.260
Line up. Line up.

00:37:58.260 --> 00:37:59.580
We're in line, we're in line.

00:37:59.700 --> 00:38:00.620
The kid just ran off to pee.

00:38:00.620 --> 00:38:02.140
Look, we almost lost first place.

00:38:02.740 --> 00:38:03.740
Our bowl's been sitting right here.

00:38:03.740 --> 00:38:04.580
We're in line.

00:38:06.020 --> 00:38:06.900
Come on, come on.

00:38:07.980 --> 00:38:09.980
Hand in the kid's meal ticket.

00:38:10.100 --> 00:38:11.540
I'll pay you when I get my wages.

00:38:11.900 --> 00:38:12.740
No running a tab.

00:38:12.900 --> 00:38:14.140
Oh, Qiu, you...

00:38:14.140 --> 00:38:15.020
You asking for a scolding again?

00:38:15.020 --> 00:38:16.740
♪Braised pork,
steamed pork with rice flour♪

00:38:16.740 --> 00:38:18.820
♪There's barely any meat in there♪

00:38:18.900 --> 00:38:20.780
♪There's barely any meat in there♪

00:38:20.900 --> 00:38:22.860
♪Stewed noodles, braised cabbage♪

00:38:22.860 --> 00:38:24.500
♪There's nothing but bones♪

00:38:25.940 --> 00:38:27.180
♪Nothing but bones♪

00:38:28.100 --> 00:38:29.740
♪The cook, the one running the kitchen♪

00:38:29.740 --> 00:38:31.700
♪Big and chubby as can be♪

00:38:31.940 --> 00:38:32.780
Who are you cursing at?

00:38:33.380 --> 00:38:34.740
How'd you catch that?

00:38:34.740 --> 00:38:35.620
Sorry. Didn't mean to.

00:38:35.620 --> 00:38:37.220
I was talking about Qiu.

00:38:37.220 --> 00:38:38.820
It's obviously you, a bad influence.

00:38:38.820 --> 00:38:39.780
Don't shake. Easy now.

00:38:40.020 --> 00:38:41.300
Give me a few slices of fatty meat.

00:38:42.340 --> 00:38:43.180
Alright.

00:38:45.100 --> 00:38:47.140
The kid spoke up.
Teach her to sing later.

00:38:47.940 --> 00:38:49.740
I can't.
We're rehearsing this afternoon.

00:38:50.540 --> 00:38:51.620
Rehearse for what?

00:38:52.980 --> 00:38:54.460
Go on, go eat over there.

00:38:55.980 --> 00:38:57.300
Making a living in perform opera

00:38:57.300 --> 00:38:58.700
isn't for just anyone.

00:38:59.100 --> 00:39:01.460
It depends if heaven gave you that gift.

00:39:02.660 --> 00:39:03.500
In here,

00:39:04.060 --> 00:39:06.580
every costume is a different role.

00:39:06.940 --> 00:39:09.580
Getting dressed and stepping onstage

00:39:09.820 --> 00:39:10.700
are no easy thing.

00:39:11.420 --> 00:39:13.260
To wear the lead's costume

00:39:13.260 --> 00:39:14.820
and stand center stage

00:39:15.620 --> 00:39:16.660
is even harder.

00:39:17.260 --> 00:39:18.620
So your first lesson

00:39:18.860 --> 00:39:20.140
is to have a goal.

00:39:20.380 --> 00:39:23.060
If you sing, be the lead.

00:39:24.860 --> 00:39:26.340
This is Li Tiemei's costume.

00:39:26.660 --> 00:39:27.780
I'm the one wearing it.

00:39:29.100 --> 00:39:30.220
As for Mi Lan,

00:39:30.220 --> 00:39:32.380
she lacks the fate and skill
to be the lead.

00:39:33.380 --> 00:39:34.620
Later, at rehearsal,

00:39:35.460 --> 00:39:37.380
don't just watch how I sing.

00:39:38.060 --> 00:39:40.860
Watch her in the audience too.

00:39:41.620 --> 00:39:42.980
See how she copies me.

00:39:43.900 --> 00:39:44.740
Of course,

00:39:44.860 --> 00:39:47.340
don't copy the envy in her eyes.

00:39:47.620 --> 00:39:48.500
Leave that part out.

00:39:49.060 --> 00:39:50.660
She's only fit to be my shadow,

00:39:51.500 --> 00:39:52.500
waiting for me

00:39:53.140 --> 00:39:54.060
to break a leg

00:39:54.380 --> 00:39:56.180
or lose my voice or something,

00:39:56.380 --> 00:39:57.820
so I can't go on or sing.

00:40:08.660 --> 00:40:10.860
One mountain can hold many sheep,

00:40:11.260 --> 00:40:13.380
but not two tigers.

00:40:13.980 --> 00:40:15.300
The stage works the same way.

00:40:15.940 --> 00:40:16.780
Got it?

00:40:24.980 --> 00:40:25.820
You're here.

00:40:26.700 --> 00:40:27.540
You came early.

00:40:27.540 --> 00:40:28.380
There you are.

00:40:31.220 --> 00:40:32.060
Morning.

00:40:32.260 --> 00:40:33.100
Morning.

00:40:35.500 --> 00:40:37.500
Sit here and watch. Watch closely.

00:40:46.540 --> 00:40:47.500
Let's begin, Director.

00:40:48.780 --> 00:40:49.620
Hua Caixiang.

00:40:50.820 --> 00:40:51.900
Let me tell you something.

00:40:52.420 --> 00:40:54.020
About tonight's show,

00:40:55.220 --> 00:40:56.060
Mi Lan is performing.

00:40:58.780 --> 00:40:59.620
Why?

00:40:59.740 --> 00:41:01.100
You've done this so many times.

00:41:01.100 --> 00:41:03.300
Give Mi Lan a chance.

00:41:04.140 --> 00:41:05.260
This is pretty sudden.

00:41:07.060 --> 00:41:09.140
Tonight's for the big leaders.

00:41:10.180 --> 00:41:11.020
Well,

00:41:13.540 --> 00:41:15.020
tonight's performance

00:41:15.420 --> 00:41:17.380
reflects on the whole troupe,

00:41:18.220 --> 00:41:20.300
so we must be careful with casting.

00:41:21.460 --> 00:41:23.180
About that rumor involving you,

00:41:23.500 --> 00:41:24.900
the impact has been very bad.

00:41:25.020 --> 00:41:26.460
Until it's fully cleared up,

00:41:26.900 --> 00:41:29.300
the organization has decided
to stop all your gigs.

00:41:30.900 --> 00:41:31.740
Director Huang,

00:41:32.420 --> 00:41:33.420
how can you

00:41:33.780 --> 00:41:34.820
and your family both

00:41:35.100 --> 00:41:36.060
fall for that flirting thing?

00:41:37.140 --> 00:41:37.980
Hua Caixiang,

00:41:37.980 --> 00:41:39.380
you need to trust the organization.

00:41:39.940 --> 00:41:42.260
We'll find who started that rumor.

00:41:42.940 --> 00:41:44.540
Then I'm really curious.

00:41:44.940 --> 00:41:48.380
Did the anonymous letter
mention my name?

00:41:49.300 --> 00:41:50.820
If it didn't,

00:41:50.820 --> 00:41:51.900
then about the heroine,

00:41:51.900 --> 00:41:53.820
if both the A-cast

00:41:53.820 --> 00:41:55.980
and the B-cast are leads,

00:41:56.660 --> 00:41:58.380
then nobody needs to sing at all.

00:41:58.620 --> 00:41:59.680
Let's switch the show, Director.

00:41:59.860 --> 00:42:01.460
Taking Tiger Mountain by Strategy.

00:42:01.460 --> 00:42:02.380
Hua Caixiang.

00:42:03.140 --> 00:42:05.300
Director Huang got the worst of it.

00:42:06.020 --> 00:42:07.580
He wanted everyone to improve

00:42:08.020 --> 00:42:09.940
and spoke to them one by one, right?

00:42:10.380 --> 00:42:11.580
He talked to one of the women,

00:42:11.580 --> 00:42:13.140
and got used by someone instead.

00:42:13.140 --> 00:42:14.620
He's the biggest victim here.

00:42:14.620 --> 00:42:15.460
Hu Sanyuan.

00:42:16.340 --> 00:42:18.020
Drop the sarcasm, will you?

00:42:18.020 --> 00:42:18.900
Director Huang,

00:42:19.340 --> 00:42:21.460
I'm honestly speaking up for you.

00:42:21.460 --> 00:42:23.300
How's that sarcasm to you?

00:42:23.860 --> 00:42:25.420
Let me play the drum tonight.

00:42:25.860 --> 00:42:26.900
What are you doing?

00:42:26.900 --> 00:42:28.180
You hate the show and doze off drumming.

00:42:28.180 --> 00:42:29.700
I'm not sleepy. I'll play it.

00:42:30.620 --> 00:42:31.860
At my level,

00:42:32.660 --> 00:42:33.500
it should be...

00:42:36.300 --> 00:42:37.140
Director Huang.

00:42:37.260 --> 00:42:38.900
Director Huang, what do you think?

00:42:39.860 --> 00:42:41.060
Even Mi Lan would get on stage.

00:42:41.060 --> 00:42:43.380
How about I play for the leaders?

00:42:43.380 --> 00:42:44.500
As for creative matters,

00:42:45.060 --> 00:42:46.420
Deputy Director Zhu decides.

00:42:47.020 --> 00:42:47.860
Director Zhu,

00:42:48.020 --> 00:42:48.860
what do you think?

00:42:50.340 --> 00:42:52.540
Hu Sanyuan is the band leader.

00:42:52.660 --> 00:42:54.580
Band matters are his call.

00:42:54.580 --> 00:42:55.540
His call?

00:42:55.540 --> 00:42:56.980
That guy wouldn't let me play.

00:42:56.980 --> 00:42:58.620
How am I worse than him?

00:42:58.620 --> 00:42:59.700
Am I worse than him?

00:42:59.860 --> 00:43:01.660
He Dachui's drumming is a mess.

00:43:02.260 --> 00:43:03.820
If he plays, I can't sing.

00:43:05.020 --> 00:43:06.940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

00:43:09.020 --> 00:43:10.940
Today, I'll take you in
from the front door.

00:43:10.940 --> 00:43:13.460
Let's see who the lead is.

00:43:13.460 --> 00:43:14.860
Tonight depends on you.

00:43:14.860 --> 00:43:16.180
For no reason at all,

00:43:16.180 --> 00:43:17.500
now, we can't even perform.

00:43:17.500 --> 00:43:18.140
Just you wait.

00:43:18.140 --> 00:43:20.180
Tonight, I'll pound the drum to pieces.

00:43:20.180 --> 00:43:21.660
Why are you freaking out like this?

00:43:21.660 --> 00:43:22.540
The scenery plank.

00:43:22.540 --> 00:43:23.500
The one with the character Xi.

00:43:23.500 --> 00:43:24.140
Give me the kid.

00:43:24.940 --> 00:43:26.220
Why put up a scarecrow?

00:43:26.540 --> 00:43:27.220
Who did it?

00:43:27.220 --> 00:43:28.620
I finally found

00:43:28.620 --> 00:43:30.500
that feeling when the drumbeat
hits just right.

00:43:30.500 --> 00:43:31.740
So, you're Hu Sanyuan?

00:43:31.740 --> 00:43:32.380
What's this about?

00:43:32.380 --> 00:43:33.100
Come with us.

00:43:37.000 --> 00:43:41.620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

00:43:43.090 --> 00:43:47.930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

00:43:49.370 --> 00:43:53.560
♪We met and brushed past♪

00:43:55.120 --> 00:44:02.420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

00:44:16.790 --> 00:44:20.540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

00:44:22.140 --> 00:44:27.710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

00:44:28.830 --> 00:44:32.890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

00:44:34.020 --> 00:44:39.610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

00:44:40.770 --> 00:44:44.970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

00:44:46.010 --> 00:44:51.640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

00:44:52.810 --> 00:44:57.500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

00:44:58.180 --> 00:45:03.350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

00:45:04.020 --> 00:45:09.050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

00:45:10.080 --> 00:45:15.510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

00:45:15.890 --> 00:45:21.170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

00:45:22.120 --> 00:45:27.930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

00:45:27.930 --> 00:45:33.350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

00:45:33.900 --> 00:45:39.410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

00:45:39.960 --> 00:45:44.920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

00:45:45.940 --> 00:45:51.220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

00:45:52.020 --> 00:46:01.050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪